Last we saw Sam Wilson, he was gifted the iconic vibranium shield by Steve Rogers aka Captain America, in hope that he would take up the role and follow the legacy. Since then we have all waited with bated breath to see how Falcon would uphold the mantle. Is the world ready for a black Captain America? Are Steve's shoes too big to fill? Why would a man represent a country that has committed atrocities against his people? Join us as we tackle the Disney+ series The Falcon And The Winter Soldier and debate all sides of the argument of what it truly means to be Captain America. Oh, and Bucky is there too! Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [ComicBookClique.com](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media. Send us feedback at ComicBookClique@Gmail.com! You Are Worthy! Please [SUPPORT US ON PATREON](http://Patreon.com/CBCClubhouse)!

